# üìò SECTION 4: Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 Database Creation & Access Lifecycle

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[App calls getWritableDatabase] --> B{DB file exists on disk?}
    B -- No --> C[Open or create the .db file]
    C --> D[Read DATABASE_VERSION from file]
    D --> E{File version newer than code version?}
    E -- Yes --> F[Throw SQLiteException]
    E -- No --> G{Code version newer than file version?}
    G -- Yes --> H[Invoke onUpgrade with old and new version]
    G -- No --> I[Database ready, no migration]
    H --> J[Run ALTER or DROP and CREATE]
    J --> K[onCreate if tables missing]
    I --> K
    B -- Yes --> L[Open existing file]
    L --> M{Version mismatch?}
    M -- Yes --> H
    M -- No --> N[Database handle returned to app]
    K --> N
    N --> O[App performs insert, update, delete, or query]
    O --> P[Cursor returned for SELECT]
```

---

## 4.2 CRUD Operation Functional Flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph WriteOps[Write Operations]
        I1[App packs ContentValues] --> I2[SQLiteDatabase insert]
        I2 --> I3[Row written to .db file]
        I2 -.return.-> I4[new row id]
        U1[App packs ContentValues with new data] --> U2[SQLiteDatabase update with WHERE]
        U2 --> I3
        U2 -.return.-> U3[count of rows affected]
        D1[App builds WHERE clause with arguments] --> D2[SQLiteDatabase delete]
        D2 --> I3
        D2 -.return.-> D3[count of rows deleted]
    end

    subgraph ReadOps[Read Operations]
        Q1[App builds projection and selection] --> Q2[SQLiteDatabase query or rawQuery]
        Q2 --> Q3[Cursor pointer positioned before first row]
        Q3 --> Q4[moveToNext loop]
        Q4 --> Q5[getString or getDouble or getLong]
        Q5 --> Q6[Cursor close in finally block]
    end
```

---

## 4.3 IoT Sensor Pipeline with SQLite as Offline Buffer

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    S[Physical IoT Sensor: temperature humidity soil] --> MC[Microcontroller: ESP32 or Arduino]
    MC -->|BLE or Wi-Fi| MOB[Android Mobile App receives JSON]
    MOB --> DEC[Parser converts JSON to SensorReading POJO]
    DEC --> SQL[SQLite insert via SQLiteOpenHelper]
    SQL --> DB[(Local .db file on device)]
    DB -->|Wi-Fi available| SYNC[Background SyncWorker uploads to cloud]
    DB -->|Wi-Fi unavailable| HOLD[Data retained locally]
    SYNC --> CLOUD[(Cloud MQTT broker or REST API)]
    HOLD --> SYNC
```

> [!NOTE]
> This block-diagram pattern is what KTU expects when a question asks to "illustrate the role of SQLite in an IoT mobile application" ‚Äî focus on the **offline-first buffer + eventual sync** concept.

---

## 4.4 Class-Responsibility Mapping

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Application Layer
        A1[MainActivity or Fragment]
        A2[ViewModel or Repository]
    end

    subgraph Helper Layer
        H1[SQLiteOpenHelper subclass]
        H2[onCreate, onUpgrade lifecycle]
    end

    subgraph Engine Layer
        E1[SQLiteDatabase]
        E2[Cursor]
        E3[ContentValues]
    end

    subgraph Native Layer
        N1[libsqlite.so C library]
        N2[DB file on internal storage]
    end

    A1 --> A2
    A2 --> H1
    H1 --> H2
    H1 --> E1
    E1 --> E3
    E1 --> E2
    E1 --> N1
    N1 --> N2
```

