#### **Part (b) ‚Äî Comparison [7 marks]**

| Feature | SharedPreferences | SQLite | Room (Jetpack) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Data Model | Key-Value pairs | Relational tables | Relational tables with ORM |
| Best For | Settings, flags | Structured, queryable data | Structured data with compile-time safety |
| Querying | None | Full SQL | SQL via DAO methods |
| Thread Safety | `commit`/`apply` semantics | Single-thread recommended; transactions for concurrency | Built-in with Executors / RxJava |
| Schema Migration | N/A | Manual via `onUpgrade` | Auto via `Migration` classes |
| Boilerplate | Low | Medium | Low (annotation-based) |
| Learning Curve | Trivial | Moderate | Moderate-High |
| IoT Fit | Device prefs | Telemetry, history | When code maintainability matters |

**When to prefer SQLite:**
- You need **complex queries** (joins, aggregation, indexing on time-series).
- You are storing **large volumes of sensor data** (thousands of rows).
- You are **offline-first** and must sync later.
- You cannot afford the additional Room dependency or want a **zero-dep** solution.

**When NOT to prefer SQLite:**
- Just storing a single boolean preference (use `SharedPreferences`).
- The team has standardized on Room and wants compile-time SQL validation.

