## üßÝ Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Last-Minute Revision Checklist)

- ‚úÖ SQLite is **embedded**, **serverless**, **ACID-compliant**, and **zero-config**.
- ‚úÖ Always extend `SQLiteOpenHelper` ‚Äî never directly call `openOrCreateDatabase()` in app code.
- ‚úÖ Two lifecycle methods: **`onCreate()`** (first-time DDL) and **`onUpgrade()`** (schema migration).
- ‚úÖ `DATABASE_VERSION` integer controls when `onUpgrade()` is triggered.
- ‚úÖ **CRUD APIs:** `insert`, `query`/`rawQuery`, `update`, `delete` ‚Äî all on `SQLiteDatabase`.
- ‚úÖ Use **`?` placeholders + `selectionArgs`** to prevent SQL injection.
- ‚úÖ `ContentValues` = write form; `Cursor` = read result slip.
- ‚úÖ Always **`cursor.close()`** in a `finally` block.
- ‚úÖ Use **`beginTransaction()` / `setTransactionSuccessful()` / `endTransaction()`** for bulk operations (~100√ó faster).
- ‚úÖ SQLite has **5 storage classes**: NULL, INTEGER, REAL, TEXT, BLOB.
- ‚úÖ **Booleans ‚Üí INTEGER 0/1**; **Dates ‚Üí TEXT (ISO 8601) or INTEGER (epoch ms)**.
- ‚úÖ DB file location: `/data/data/<package>/databases/<name>.db`.
- ‚úÖ For IoT: SQLite acts as an **offline buffer** between sensors and the cloud sync layer.
- ‚úÖ Room is the modern Jetpack abstraction over SQLite ‚Äî but understanding raw SQLite is mandatory for KTU.
- ‚úÖ `nullColumnHack` parameter is required by the `insert()` signature ‚Äî pass `null` if you supply all required columns.

